T1  - A Bayesian approach to testing portfolio efficiency
AU  - Shanken, Jay
JO  - Journal of Financial Economics
VL  - 19
IS  - 2
SP  - 195
EP  - 215
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/12/01/
SN  - 0304-405X
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-405X(87)90002-X
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304405X8790002X
AB  - This paper develops a Bayesian test of portfolio efficiency and derives a computationally convenient posterior-odds ratio. The analysis indicates that significance levels higher than the traditional 0.05 level are recommended for many test situations. In an example from the literature, the classical test fails to reject with p-value 0.082, yet the odds are nearly two to one against efficiency under apparently reasonable assumptions. Procedures for testing approximate efficiency and for aggregating subperiod results are also considered.
